title: [Triskele, West Corridor]
description: Stout modwir timbers are symmetrically spaced between walls of precisely fitted stone blocks, each carved with a detailed bas-relief scene depicting battle with orcs, ogres, or trolls.  Shining down through glaes panel skylights of irregular thickness, sunlight dances over the carvings, creating an illusion of movement.  Corridors branch off to the northwest and southwest, while the entrance lies to the east.
